 add the reflect-config manually. I need to think about whether to use the direct adapter or the Javac task to handle this. Getting to line 96 requires accessing the sun class, and I wonder if using the Javac task will help it scan the actual source files effectively. It’s a bit tricky with the mock compiler — it won’t compile, but I hope the reflection in CompilerAdapterFactory works out for instantiating Javac12 appropriately.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating compiler integration options**\\n\\nI’m thinking the dynamic access class might be CompilerAdapterFactory, but I wonder if it’s already covered. If I go with the direct Javac12, it feels more focused since I can use the public adapter API to invoke it. To fill the compileList, I think using the Javac task is better since it populates the fileList correctly. The existing tests focus on a fully qualified Jikes implementation, and I’m curious about testing behavior—like if the fake classic compiler runs successfully, but will it verify the output?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering package and test setup**\\n\\nI need to think about the package being `sun.*` and how Checkstyle might react. Maybe I could avoid using qualified imports, but existing style prefers importing classes directly. However, using `sun.tools.javac.Main` doesn’t involve reflection, which might complicate module compilation. I should probably prepare a native image reflection config for public constructors and methods. I also need to ensure the test doesn’t hardcode any versions, and I wonder about concurrency—should static fields be reset before tests run?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LpNvuAVdKBHEYI6HDU5iAhcB|fc_0f1369d971afdbfe0169effcd69f188193b5abfc3382052d30", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/Javac12Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage ant.ant;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.Project;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Javac;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.compilers.Javac12;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\nimport sun.tools.javac.Main;\n\npublic class Javac12Test {\n    @BeforeEach\n    void resetClassicCompiler() {\n        Main.reset();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void invokesClassicCompilerThroughLegacyAdapter(@TempDir Path temporaryDirectory) throws IOException {\n        Path sourceDirectory = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"src\");\n        Path destinationDirectory = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"classes\");\n        Files.createDirectories(sourceDirectory);\n        Files.createDirectories(destinationDirectory);\n        Path sourceFile = sourceDirectory.resolve(\"ClassicGreeting.java\");\n        Files.write(sourceFile, classicGreetingSource().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n\n        RecordingJavac javac = newClassicJavacTask(sourceDirectory, destinationDirectory, sourceFile.toFile());\n        Javac12 adapter = new Javac12();\n        adapter.setJavac(javac);\n\n        assertThat(adapter.execute()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(Main.getLastProgramName()).isEqualTo(\"javac\");\n        assertThat(Arrays.asList(Main.getLastArguments()))\n            .contains(\"-d\", destinationDirectory.toFile().getAbsolutePath(), sourceFile.toFile().getAbsolutePath());\n    }\n\n    private static RecordingJavac newClassicJavacTask(Path sourceDirectory, Path destinationDirectory, File sourceFile) {\n        Project project = new Project();\n        project.init();\n        project.setBaseDir(sourceDirectory.getParent().toFile());\n\n        RecordingJavac javac = new RecordingJavac();\n        javac.setProject(project);\n        javac.setTaskName(\"javac\");\n        javac.setSrcdir(new org.apache.tools.ant.types.Path(project, sourceDirectory.toString()));\n        javac.setDestdir(destinationDirectory.toFile());\n        javac.setIncludeantruntime(false);\n        javac.setIncludejavaruntime(false);\n        javac.setCompileList(sourceFile);\n        return javac;\n    }\n\n    private static String classicGreetingSource() {\n        return \"public class ClassicGreeting {\\n\"\n            + \"    public String message() {\\n\"\n            + \"        return \\\"hello\\\";\\n\"\n            + \"    }\\n\"\n            + \"}\\n\";\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingJavac extends Javac {\n        void setCompileList(File... files) {\n            compileList = files;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 651, "output": 2038, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32897, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777335490579, "responseId": "resp_0f1369d971afdbfe0169effcc30d9081939382eeb47bbfebca"}}
